1588<div>

1589<h3>

1590A Fresh Take on Modern Decor</h3>

1591

1592

1593<p>

1594After you furnish a room, it&rsquo;s time to make it truly yours with decor that speaks to your style. Choose heirloom-quality art, lamps, and mirrors to add modern elegance to your space.&nbsp;</p>

1595

1596

1597<h4>

1598Use Accessories to Heighten Interest</h4>

1599

1600

1601<p>

1602Brighten up your space with decorative pillows in a variety of materials, like wool, linen, or cotton. Try throw pillows with a modern take on a vintage design, such as a mudcloth or embroidered pattern. The perfect couch pillow or throw blanket provides just the right amount of elegance for every room.</p>

1603

1604

1605<p>

1606Choose eye-catching round mirrors inlaid with brass, or area rugs, and wooden baskets. You could even experiment with different mirror shapes, like square, circular, or the traditional rectangular. Try a backlit mirror if the room is naturally dark. Not sure where to hang your new mirror? Give it a place on your gallery wall, above the fireplace, or in the entryway for moments of reflection.</p>

1607

1608

1609<h4>

1610Staying True to Your Decor Style</h4>

1611

1612

1613<p>

1614Minimalism is just one of the latest trends, but if different shades of beige aren&rsquo;t for you, try experimenting with pops of color and high-quality art. Maybe you want to add to your eclectic painting collection, or maybe you&rsquo;re looking for the perfect original piece to round out your gallery wall. Either way, Vevano Art Studio has pieces that complement your existing decor and make you feel right at home.</p>

1615

1616

1617<h4>

1618Art as the Centerpiece</h4>

1619

1620

1621<p>

1622Vevano Home has partnered with Four Hands Art Collective to deliver a collection of curated pieces for every taste. After you order a piece of art from this heirloom collection, it comes shipped to your door matted, framed, and ready to hang. Each artist is masterfully trained in styles ranging from abstract to modern. If you&rsquo;re trying to shy away from bolder colors, the collection also includes striking black and white photography as well.</p>

1623

1624

1625<h4>

1626Lighting Up Your Space</h4>

1627

1628

1629<p>

1630The glow of ambient light adds the intimate touch every room needs to make it complete. Choose from LED table lamps, flexible desk lamps for easy reading, or lovely floor lamps to illuminate your living room. Choose a bulb that casts a complementary glow on your large area rug or pillow set.&nbsp;</p>

1631

1632

1633<h4>

1634Contemporary Storage Solutions</h4>

1635

1636

1637<p>

1638We all need places to store our things, but storing them in a way that blends in seamlessly with the decor isn&rsquo;t always easy. Try decorative baskets with or without lids, or even a wall shelf unit for a stack of books. Don&rsquo;t have a wine cellar? Use a wall wine rack to display your collection and keep it close for easy access.</p>

1639

1640

1641<p>

1642Are you running out of space for your many subscriptions? Try a sleek magazine rack in the corner next to your woven baskets or reading lamp. Magazine storage doesn&rsquo;t have to be clunky or cluttered.&nbsp;<br />

1643

1644&nbsp;</p>

1645

1646</div>

you furnish a room, it\u0026rsquo;s time to make it truly yours with decor that speaks to your style. Choose heirloom-quality art, lamps, and mirrors to add modern elegance to your space.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eUse Accessories to Heighten Interest\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBrighten up your space with decorative pillows in a variety of materials, like wool, linen, or cotton. Try throw pillows with a modern take on a vintage design, such as a mudcloth or embroidered pattern. The perfect couch pillow or throw blanket provides just the right amount of elegance for every room.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChoose eye-catching round mirrors inlaid with brass, or area rugs, and wooden baskets. You could even experiment with different mirror shapes, like square, circular, or the traditional rectangular. Try a backlit mirror if the room is naturally dark. Not sure where to hang your new mirror? Give it a place on your gallery wall, above the fireplace, or in the entryway for moments of reflection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eStaying True to Your Decor Style\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMinimalism is just one of the latest trends, but if different shades of beige aren\u0026rsquo;t for you, try experimenting with pops of color and high-quality art. Maybe you want to add to your eclectic painting collection, or maybe you\u0026rsquo;re looking for the perfect original piece to round out your gallery wall. Either way, Vevano Art Studio has pieces that complement your existing decor and make you feel right at home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eArt as the Centerpiece\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eVevano Home has partnered with Four Hands Art Collective to deliver a collection of curated pieces for every taste. After you order a piece of art from this heirloom collection, it comes shipped to your door matted, framed, and ready to hang. Each artist is masterfully trained in styles ranging from abstract to modern. If you\u0026rsquo;re trying to shy away from bolder colors, the collection also includes striking black and white photography as well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eLighting Up Your Space\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe glow of ambient light adds the intimate touch every room needs to make it complete. Choose from LED table lamps, flexible desk lamps for easy reading, or lovely floor lamps to illuminate your living room. Choose a bulb that casts a complementary glow on your large area rug or pillow set.\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch4\u003eContemporary Storage Solutions\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe all need places to store our things, but storing them in a way that blends in seamlessly with the decor isn\u0026rsquo;t always easy. Try decorative baskets with or without lids, or even a wall shelf unit for a stack of books. Don\u0026rsquo;t have a wine cellar? Use a wall wine rack to display your collection and keep it close for easy access.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAre you running out of space for your many subscriptions? Try a sleek magazine rack in the corner next to your woven baskets or reading lamp. Magazine storage doesn\u0026rsquo;t have to be clunky or cluttered.\u0026nbsp;\u003cbr
